{"name": "corsikaio", "metadata": {"name": "corsikaio", "version": "0.5.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://github.com/cta-observatory/corsikaio", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["numpy"], "summary": "Reader for corsika binary output files using numpy", "upload_time": 1730738416}, "documentation": ["# pycorsikaio [![CI](https://github.com/cta-observatory/pycorsikaio/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/cta-observatory/pycorsikaio/actions/workflows/ci.yml) [![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/corsikaio.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/corsikaio)\n\n\nPython module to read the CORSIKA binary output files.\n\n## Install\n\nRun\n```\npip install corsikaio\n```\n\n## Features\n\nLoad CORSIKA binary particle or cherenkov data files using python and numpy.\n\nAlso supports MMCS 6.5\n\n```python\nfrom corsikaio import CorsikaCherenkovFile\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\n\nwith CorsikaCherenkovFile('cer000001') as f:\n    print(f.run_header['run_number'])\n    print(f.version)\n\n    for e in f:\n        print(e.header['total_energy'])\n        \n        plt.scatter(e.photons['x'], e.photons['y'])\n        plt.show()\n```\n\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "corsikaio.constants", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "corsikaio.constants.BLOCK_SIZE_FLOATS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.constants.BLOCK_SIZE_FLOATS_THIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.constants.BLOCK_SIZE_BYTES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.constants.BLOCK_SIZE_BYTES_THIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.constants.RUNH_VERSION_POSITION", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.constants.EVTH_VERSION_POSITION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.io", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "corsikaio.io.is_gzip", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Test if a file is gzipped by reading its first two bytes and compare\nto the gzip marker bytes."]}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.is_zstd", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Test if a file is compressed using zstd using its magic marker bytes\n    "]}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.open_compressed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.read_buffer_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Reads the first 4 bytes of a file and checks if\nit is the 'RUNH' designation None is returned,\nif not interpret it as unsigned integer, the\nsize of the CORSIKA buffer in bytes"]}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.iter_blocks", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "thinning", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.read_block", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "thinning", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "buffer_size", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Reads a block of CORSIKA output, e.g. 273 4-byte floats.\n\nUnder some conditions, CORSIKA writes output as FORTRAN\nraw file format. This means, there is a 4-byte unsigned\ninteger (the buffer size)\nbefore and after each block, which has to be skipped."]}], "variables": [{"name": "corsikaio.io.DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.DEFAULT_BUFFER_SIZE_THIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.io.RECORD_MARKER", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal", "documentation": ["Functions related to the CORSIKA longitudinal distribution"], "functions": [{"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.longitudinal_fit_function", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "depth", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "n_max", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "depth_0", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "depth_max", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "c", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["The function CORSIKA fits to the longitudinal distribution.\n\nParameters of this function are stored in the event end block\nin case the corresponding options of the LONGI keyword are set.\n\nUse like this:\n\n```pycon\n>>> depth = np.linspace(0, 1000, 100)\n>>> longitudinal_fit_function(depth, *event.end[\"longitudinal_fit_parameters\"])\n```\n"]}, {"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.read_longitudinal_distributions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Read longitudinal profiles from CORSIKA longitudinal file.\n\nThis function returns a generator that iterates over air showers.\n\nParameters\n----------\npath : str, Path\n    Path to CORSIKA longitudinal output file (DATXXXXXX.long)\n\nYields\n------\nlongitudinal : dict\n    Dict with the information for one air shower.\n    Contains the longitudinal tables for \"particles\" and \"energy_deposition\"\n    and the \"parameters\", \"chi2_ndf\" and \"average_deviation\" values of the \n    fit to the distribution if available."]}], "variables": [{"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.PARTICLE_HEADER_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.ENERGY_HEADER_RE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.ENERGY_COLUMNS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "corsikaio.longitudinal.PARTICLE_COLUMNS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "class